parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, or even complete engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.

The failure of the head gaskets can cause engine coolant to leak into the engine, leading to engine damage, overheating, or even complete engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.

The failure of the accessory belts (such as the serpentine belt) can cause the engine to overheat, the air conditioning to malfunction, and other engine components to fail, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the timing chain can cause engine damage, stalling, or even complete engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.

Heater core failure can cause smoke to pour out of the dashboard, potentially leading to a fire hazard, and can also cause coolant to leak into the passenger compartment, leading to poor visibility and a risk of accidents.
symptoms: Smoke pouring out of the dashboard
coolant odor in the passenger compartment

the seat belt will not retract
